Let P represent the number of pink gumballs we need to find. From the problem statement, it follows that;
P = 4*B + 22     [because P is 22 more than four times the amount of B]  ........(equation)
Substituting equation into itself using value provided i.e., B=9913180 yields;
P = 4*(9913180)+22
Solving this expression provides us with ;
P = 39652720+22
We sum up these numbers obtaining :
P = 39652742 .
